Rakuen has developed a pragmatic tolerance for cipher tradition practitioners rooted in the city's chronic resource constraints. The Eccentric Woodland corridor — primary route between Midgaard and Rakuen — has been one of the cipher tradition's most active operating zones since the Ash-and-Iron Decades; route guide expertise is at maximum premium in the Woodland's disorienting terrain, and the city has more need for reliable route intelligence than it has capacity to pay premium prices for official escort. Garden Ledger Clerks who maintain Rakuen's documentary evidence of Midgaard's Violet Compact era have found, on occasion, that cipher tradition practitioners with archive access expertise make useful research partners — a relationship that Rakuen's leadership acknowledges at one remove while not formalizing. The city's Ember Warden collective accountability framework creates tension with the tradition's non-institutional orientation, but resource necessity consistently overrides theoretical purity.

