Mafdet's Shrine of the First Claw creates a comprehensive map of what one can do in Mafdet while remaining below swift-court jurisdiction, which cipher tradition practitioners have studied carefully. The three-route Saltglass Reach system — Swift Line, Heavy Road, and Sealed Route — generates distinct markets for each of the tradition's three lineages: convoy timing intelligence (route guides), manifest-adjacent cargo movement (fence operators), and Ledger House authorization documentation (private intelligence dealers). The Strandline Compact's Sealed Route provisions, which require Mafdet authorization for high-security cargo, create the most lucrative and most legally sensitive market for private intelligence dealer skills in the five-city network. Harbor Wardens' Ledger Houses document economic activity comprehensively enough that Mafdet is simultaneously the most challenging operating environment for the tradition and the one with the highest value targets.

