Khenari sacred record practice requires that identity be correctly established for documentation to have spiritual validity. The private intelligence dealer lineage's document forgery and identity substitution work intersects directly with Khenari documentation requirements: a forged identity document that passes civic registry review may not pass Khenari spiritual record assessment, which uses different verification methods rooted in death-rite documentation and bloodline record rather than civic credential formats. Khenari clerics in Midgaard's temple districts have developed detection protocols for what they call "document-ghost identities" — records with civic validity but no corresponding spiritual documentation chain. The Sealed Names Apparatus has expressed interest in these detection protocols through intermediaries but has not formalized an information-sharing arrangement, because the arrangement would require acknowledging that the Apparatus's own records contain document-ghost entries that it created.

